message.content: Papilio garamas is a species of butterfly belonging to the Papilionidae family. The wingspan of Papilio garamas ranges from 7 to 9 cm. The upper side of the wings is black with yellow and blue markings. The underside of the wings is a subdued combination of light and dark tones of brown. The body is black with white spots on the thorax and abdomen. Papilio garamas can be found in subtropical and tropical areas of Southeast Asia. The species is known for its beautiful and intricate wing patterns, making it a popular subject for butterfly enthusiasts and collectors. In the wild, Papilio garamas feeds on the nectar of flowers, while the larvae feed on the leaves of citrus plants.
